methods.getTimeZone:
Returns the underlying Joda time zone for this TimeZone.

:return: (org.joda.time.DateTimeZone) the underlying Joda time zone.
methods.getTzDefault:
Get the default time zone.

:return: (io.deephaven.time.TimeZone) the default TimeZone
methods.lookup:
Find the corresponding TimeZone for a given Joda DateTimeZone.

:param dateTimeZone: (org.joda.time.DateTimeZone) - the time zone to search for
:return: (io.deephaven.time.TimeZone) the corresponding TimeZone, or null if none was found
methods.setTzDefault:
Set the default time zone.

:param tzDefault: (io.deephaven.time.TimeZone) - the TimeZone to be used as the default.
methods.valueOf:
Returns the enum constant of this type with the specified name.
The string must match exactly an identifier used to declare an
enum constant in this type.  (Extraneous whitespace characters are 
not permitted.)

:param name: (java.lang.String) - the name of the enum constant to be returned.
:return: (io.deephaven.time.TimeZone) the enum constant with the specified name
methods.values:
Returns an array containing the constants of this enum type, in
the order they are declared.

:return: (io.deephaven.time.TimeZone[]) an array containing the constants of this enum type, in the order they are declared
methods.valuesByOffset:
This method returns the same contents as values(), but ordered by geographic location / UTC
 offset. If two elements exist within the same timezone, they are second-order-sorted by name

:return: (io.deephaven.time.TimeZone[]) An array of TimeZones ordered by UTC-offset

text: Defines Deephaven-supported timezones, which may be used for PQ-scheduling and display purposes
